{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775849149251,"sessionID":"ses_28724eb1bffexGvVie186Cb16M","part":{"id":"prt_d78db9305001hgq2Gsfi5Br698","messageID":"msg_d78db775400170ALOu87CV2PtB","sessionID":"ses_28724eb1bffexGvVie186Cb16M","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-598edb2fa8164236bed87b1024c864c9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/common/types/sandbox.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/common/types/sandbox.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package types\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"fmt\"\n5: \t\"time\"\n6: )\n7: \n8: const (\n9: \tAgentRuntimeKind    = \"AgentRuntime\"\n10: \tCodeInterpreterKind = \"CodeInterpreter\"\n11: \tSandboxKind         = \"Sandbox\"\n12: \tSandboxClaimKind    = \"SandboxClaim\"\n13: )\n14: \n15: type CreateSandboxRequest struct {\n16: \tKind      string `json:\"kind\"`\n17: \tName      string `json:\"name\"`\n18: \tNamespace string `json:\"namespace\"`\n19: }\n20: \n21: func (r *CreateSandboxRequest) Validate() error {\n22: \tif r.Kind != AgentRuntimeKind && r.Kind != CodeInterpreterKind {\n23: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"kind must be %s or %s\", AgentRuntimeKind, CodeInterpreterKind)\n24: \t}\n25: \tif r.Namespace == \"\" {\n26: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"namespace is required\")\n27: \t}\n28: \tif r.Name == \"\" {\n29: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"name is required\")\n30: \t}\n31: \treturn nil\n32: }\n33: \n34: type CreateSandboxResponse struct {\n35: \tSessionID   string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n36: \tSandboxID   string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n37: \tSandboxName string              `json:\"sandboxName\"`\n38: \tEntryPoints []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n39: }\n40: \n41: type SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n42: \tPath     string `json:\"path\"`\n43: \tProtocol string `json:\"protocol\"`\n44: \tEndpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"`\n45: }\n46: \n47: type SandboxInfo struct {\n48: \tKind               string              `json:\"kind\"`\n49: \tSandboxID          string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n50: \tSandboxNamespace   string              `json:\"sandboxNamespace\"`\n51: \tSandboxName        string              `json:\"sandboxName\"`\n52: \tName               string              `json:\"name\"`\n53: \tSessionID          string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n54: \tCreatedAt          time.Time           `json:\"createdAt\"`\n55: \tExpiresAt          time.Time           `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n56: \tStatus             string              `json:\"status\"`\n57: \tEntryPoints        []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n58: \tUserToken          string              `json:\"userToken,omitempty\"`\n59: \tServiceAccount     string              `json:\"serviceAccount,omitempty\"`\n60: \tServiceAccountName string              `json:\"serviceAccountName,omitempty\"`\n61: \tLastActivity       time.Time           `json:\"lastActivity,omitempty\"`\n62: }\n\n(End of file - total 62 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package types\n\nimport (\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"time\"\n)\n\nconst (\n\tAgentRuntimeKind    = \"AgentRuntime\"\n\tCodeInterpreterKind = \"CodeInterpreter\"\n\tSandboxKind         = \"Sandbox\"\n\tSandboxClaimKind    = \"SandboxClaim\"\n)\n\ntype CreateSandboxRequest struct {\n\tKind      string `json:\"kind\"`\n\tName      string `json:\"name\"`\n\tNamespace string `json:\"namespace\"`\n}\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/common/types/sandbox.go","time":{"start":1775849149229,"end":1775849149249}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775849149253,"sessionID":"ses_28724eb1bffexGvVie186Cb16M","part":{"id":"prt_d78db8b74001OBcttMrHI3YOKi","messageID":"msg_d78db775400170ALOu87CV2PtB","sessionID":"ses_28724eb1bffexGvVie186Cb16M","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-430e8da7bc5b4fd4a16312515ca56e29","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-008/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-008/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制\n2: \n3: **Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** S\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Define the Sandbox Garbage Collector that periodically scans and deletes expired and idle sandboxes. The GC runs as a background goroutine with configurable intervals, enforces TTL via `ExpiresAt` timestamps, handles idle timeout cleanup via `LastActivity`, and limits batch operations to prevent cluster overload.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: GarbageCollector type definition\n18: \n19: The system SHALL define `GarbageCollector` as a background process for periodic sandbox cleanup.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: GarbageCollector struct definition\n22: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n23: - **WHEN** reading the `GarbageCollector` struct\n24: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n25:   - `manager *SandboxLifecycleManager` for sandbox deletion delegation\n26:   - `interval time.Duration` for GC cycle interval\n27:   - `onceTimeout time.Duration` for single GC cycle timeout\n28:   - `stopCh chan struct{}` for graceful shutdown signal\n29:   - `wg sync.WaitGroup` for goroutine synchronization\n30:   - `logger Logger` for structured logging\n31:   - `idleTimeout time.Duration` for idle sandbox cleanup threshold\n32:   - `idleMu sync.RWMutex` for idleTimeout concurrent access protection\n33: \n34: #### Scenario: NewGarbageCollector constructor\n35: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n36: - **WHEN** calling `NewGarbageCollector(manager, interval, onceTimeout, logger)`\n37: - **THEN** it SHALL return `*GarbageCollector` with:\n38:   - `interval` defaulted to `GarbageCollectorInterval` (2 minutes) if zero\n39:   - `onceTimeout` defaulted to `2 * time.Minute` if zero\n40:   - `idleTimeout` initialized from `manager.config.DefaultIdleTimeout`\n41:   - `stopCh` initialized as `make(chan struct{})`\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: NewGarbageCollector with custom interval\n44: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n45: - **WHEN** calling `NewGarbageCollector(manager, 5*time.Minute, 3*time.Minute, logger)`\n46: - **THEN** it SHALL return `*GarbageCollector` with:\n47:   - `interval` = `5 * time.Minute`\n48:   - `onceTimeout` = `3 * time.Minute`\n49: \n50: ---\n51: \n52: ### Requirement: GarbageCollector lifecycle\n53: \n54: The system SHALL provide Start/Stop lifecycle methods for the GC background goroutine.\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: Start launches runLoop\n57: - **GIVEN** a `GarbageCollector` instance\n58: - **WHEN** calling `gc.Start()`\n59: - **THEN** `gc.wg.Add(1)` SHALL be called\n60: - AND `gc.runLoop()` SHALL be launched as a goroutine\n61: \n62: #### Scenario: Stop signals shutdown\n63: - **GIVEN** a running `GarbageCollector`\n64: - **WHEN** calling `gc.Stop()`\n65: - **THEN** `close(gc.stopCh)` SHALL be called\n66: - AND `gc.wg.Wait()` SHALL block until goroutine completes\n67: \n68: #### Scenario: runLoop initial execution\n69: - **GIVEN** a started `GarbageCollector`\n70: - **WHEN** `runLoop` begins\n71: - **THEN** `gc.runOnce(context.Background())` SHALL be called immediately\n72: - AND ticker SHALL be created with `time.NewTicker(gc.interval)`\n73: \n74: #### Scenario: runLoop ticker-driven execution\n75: - **GIVEN** a running `runLoop`\n76: - **WHEN** ticker fires\n77: - **THEN** `gc.runOnce(context.Background())` SHALL be called\n78: \n79: #### Scenario: runLoop stops on stopCh\n80: - **GIVEN** a running `runLoop`\n81: - **WHEN** `stopCh` receives signal\n82: - **THEN** `gc.logger.Info(\"garbage collector stopped\")` SHALL be called\n83: - AND goroutine SHALL return\n84: \n85: ---\n86: \n87: ### Requirement: runOnce GC cycle\n88: \n89: The system SHALL implement `runOnce` for a single garbage collection cycle.\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: runOnce with context timeout\n92: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n93: - **WHEN** calling `runOnce(ctx)`\n94: - **THEN** `context.WithTimeout(ctx, gc.onceTimeout)` SHALL be created\n95: - AND cancel SHALL be deferred\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: runOnce queries expired sandboxes\n98: - **GIVEN** `runOnce` execution\n99: - **WHEN** listing sandboxes for cleanup\n100: - **THEN** `gc.manager.store.ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, now, GCBatchSize)` SHALL be called\n101: - AND result SHALL be limited to `GCBatchSize=16`\n102: \n103: #### Scenario: runOnce queries inactive sandboxes\n104: - **GIVEN** `runOnce` execution\n105: - **WHEN** listing sandboxes for cleanup\n106: - **THEN** `inactiveBefore = now.Add(-idleTimeout)` SHALL be computed\n107: - AND `gc.manager.store.ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, inactiveBefore, GCBatchSize)` SHALL be called\n108: \n109: #### Scenario: runOnce deletes expired sandbox\n110: - **GIVEN** an expired sandbox with `ExpiresAt < now`\n111: - **WHEN** `runOnce` processes it\n112: - **THEN** `gc.manager.DeleteSandbox(ctx, sb.SessionID)` SHALL be called\n113: - AND deletion reason SHALL be `DeletionReasonMaxDurationReached`\n114: \n115: #### Scenario: runOnce deletes inactive sandbox\n116: - **GIVEN** an inactive sandbox with `LastActivity < inactiveBefore`\n117: - **WHEN** `runOnce` processes it\n118: - **THEN** `gc.manager.DeleteSandbox(ctx, sb.SessionID)` SHALL be called\n119: - AND deletion reason SHALL be `DeletionReasonIdleTimeout`\n120: \n121: #### Scenario: runOnce ignores NotFound error\n122: - **GIVEN** a sandbox that no longer exists\n123: - **WHEN** `DeleteSandbox` returns `NotFoundError`\n124: - **THEN** error SHALL be ignored with `continue`\n125: \n126: #### Scenario: runOnce logs deletion success\n127: - **GIVEN** a successfully deleted sandbox\n128: - **WHEN** deletion completes\n129: - **THEN** `gc.logger.Info(\"gc deleted sandbox\", \"sessionID\", ..., \"sandboxName\", ..., \"reason\", ...)` SHALL be called\n130: \n131: #### Scenario: runOnce logs deletion failure\n132: - **GIVEN** a deletion that fails (not NotFound)\n133: - **WHEN** error occurs\n134: - **THEN** `gc.logger.Error(\"gc delete failed\", \"sessionID\", ..., \"err\", ...)` SHALL be called\n135: - AND processing SHALL continue for remaining sandboxes\n136: \n137: ---\n138: \n139: ### Requirement: Batch size limitation\n140: \n141: The system SHALL limit cleanup operations per cycle to prevent cluster overload.\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: GCBatchSize constant\n144: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n145: - **WHEN** reading constants\n146: - **THEN** `GCBatchSize` SHALL be `16`\n147: \n148: #### Scenario: ListExpiredSandboxes respects limit\n149: - **GIVEN** `MemoryStore.ListExpiredSandboxes`\n150: - **WHEN** calling with `limit=16`\n151: - **THEN** result SHALL be truncated to at most `16` sandboxes\n152: - AND sandboxes SHALL be sorted by `ExpiresAt` ascending\n153: \n154: #### Scenario: ListInactiveSandboxes respects limit\n155: - **GIVEN** `MemoryStore.ListInactiveSandboxes`\n156: - **WHEN** calling with `limit=16`\n157: - **THEN** result SHALL be truncated to at most `16` sandboxes\n158: - AND sandboxes SHALL be sorted by `LastActivity` ascending\n159: \n160: #### Scenario: Combined batch limit\n161: - **GIVEN** 20 expired and 20 inactive sandboxes\n162: - **WHEN** `runOnce` executes\n163: - **THEN** at most `16 + 16 = 32` sandboxes SHALL be processed\n164: - AND remaining sandboxes SHALL be processed in subsequent cycles\n165: \n166: ---\n167: \n168: ### Requirement: Store interface extensions\n169: \n170: The system SHALL extend the Store interface with GC-specific query methods.\n171: \n172: #### Scenario: Store interface includes GC methods\n173: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go`\n174: - **WHEN** reading the `Store` interface\n175: - **THEN** interface SHALL include:\n176:   - `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n177:   - `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n178: \n179: #### Scenario: MemoryStore ListExpiredSandboxes implementation\n180: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/store.go`\n181: - **WHEN** calling `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)`\n182: - **THEN** all sandboxes with `ExpiresAt.Before(before)` SHALL be returned\n183: - AND result SHALL be sorted by `ExpiresAt` ascending\n184: - AND result SHALL be limited to `limit` entries\n185: \n186: #### Scenario: MemoryStore ListInactiveSandboxes implementation\n187: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/store.go`\n188: - **WHEN** calling `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)`\n189: - **THEN** all sandboxes with non-zero `LastActivity` and `LastActivity.Before(before)` SHALL be returned\n190: - AND result SHALL be sorted by `LastActivity` ascending\n191: - AND result SHALL be limited to `limit` entries\n192: \n193: #### Scenario: ListInactiveSandboxes skips zero LastActivity\n194: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with `LastActivity.IsZero() == true`\n195: - **WHEN** calling `ListInactiveSandboxes`\n196: - **THEN** that sandbox SHALL NOT be included in results\n197: \n198: ---\n199: \n200: ### Requirement: Runtime configuration\n201: \n202: The system SHALL support runtime configuration of GC parameters.\n203: \n204: #### Scenario: SetIdleTimeout method\n205: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n206: - **WHEN** calling `gc.SetIdleTimeout(30 * time.Minute)`\n207: - **THEN** `gc.idleMu.Lock()` SHALL be acquired\n208: - AND `gc.idleTimeout` SHALL be updated to `30 * time.Minute`\n209: - AND mutex SHALL be released\n210: \n211: #### Scenario: getIdleTimeout method\n212: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n213: - **WHEN** calling `gc.getIdleTimeout()`\n214: - **THEN** `gc.idleMu.RLock()` SHALL be acquired\n215: - AND current `idleTimeout` value SHALL be returned\n216: - AND mutex SHALL be released\n217: \n218: #### Scenario: GetStats method\n219: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n220: - **WHEN** calling `gc.GetStats()`\n221: - **THEN** `GarbageCollectorStats` SHALL be returned with:\n222:   - `Interval`: current GC cycle interval\n223:   - `OnceTimeout`: current single-cycle timeout\n224:   - `IdleTimeout`: current idle threshold\n225: \n226: #### Scenario: GarbageCollectorStats struct\n227: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n228: - **WHEN** reading `GarbageCollectorStats`\n229: - **THEN** struct SHALL contain:\n230:   - `Interval time.Duration`\n231:   - `OnceTimeout time.Duration`\n232:   - `IdleTimeout time.Duration`\n233: \n234: ---\n235: \n236: ### Requirement: Deletion reason determination\n237: \n238: The system SHALL categorize deletion reasons for logging and tracking.\n239: \n240: #### Scenario: determineDeletionReason function\n241: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go`\n242: - **WHEN** calling `determineDeletionReason(sandbox, now, idleTimeout)`\n243: - **THEN** it SHALL return `DeletionReason`\n244: \n245: #### Scenario: MaxDurationReached reason\n246: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with `now.After(sandbox.ExpiresAt)`\n247: - **WHEN** determining reason\n248: - **THEN** `DeletionReasonMaxDurationReached` SHALL be returned\n249: \n250: #### Scenario: IdleTimeout reason\n251: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with non-zero `LastActivity` and `now.After(sandbox.LastActivity.Add(idleTimeout))`\n252: - **WHEN** determining reason and `ExpiresAt` not yet reached\n253: - **THEN** `DeletionReasonIdleTimeout` SHALL be returned\n254: \n255: #### Scenario: UserRequest fallback reason\n256: - **GIVEN** a sandbox not expired and not idle\n257: - **WHEN** determining reason\n258: - **THEN** `DeletionReasonUserRequest` SHALL be returned as fallback\n259: \n260: ---\n261: \n262: ### Requirement: DeletionReason constants\n263: \n264: The system SHALL define deletion reason constants for categorization.\n265: \n266: #### Scenario: DeletionReasonIdleTimeout constant\n267: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go`\n268: - **WHEN** reading constants\n269: - **THEN** `DeletionReasonIdleTimeout` SHALL be `\"IdleTimeout\"`\n270: \n271: #### Scenario: DeletionReasonMaxDurationReached constant\n272: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go`\n273: - **WHEN** reading constants\n274: - **THEN** `DeletionReasonMaxDurationReached` SHALL be `\"MaxDurationReached\"`\n275: \n276: #### Scenario: DeletionReasonUserRequest constant\n277: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go`\n278: - **WHEN** reading constants\n279: - **THEN** `DeletionReasonUserRequest` SHALL be `\"UserRequest\"`\n280: \n281: ---\n282: \n283: ### Requirement: Default constants\n284: \n285: The system SHALL define default timeout constants.\n286: \n287: #### Scenario: GarbageCollectorInterval constant\n288: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n289: - **WHEN** reading constants\n290: - **THEN** `GarbageCollectorInterval` SHALL be `2 * time.Minute`\n291: \n292: #### Scenario: DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout constant\n293: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n294: - **WHEN** reading constants\n295: - **THEN** `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout` SHALL be `15 * time.Minute`\n296: \n297: #### Scenario: DefaultSandboxTTL constant\n298: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n299: - **WHEN** reading constants\n300: - **THEN** `DefaultSandboxTTL` SHALL be `8 * time.Hour`\n301: \n302: ---\n303: \n304: ### Requirement: Concurrent safety\n305: \n306: The system SHALL handle concurrent access safely.\n307: \n308: #### Scenario: idleMu protects idleTimeout\n309: - **GIVEN** `GarbageCollector` with `idleMu sync.RWMutex`\n310: - **WHEN** concurrent reads/writes to `idleTimeout`\n311: - **THEN** `sync.RWMutex` SHALL prevent race conditions\n312: - AND `RLock` SHALL be used for reads\n313: - AND `Lock` SHALL be used for writes\n314: \n315: #### Scenario: Store mutex protection\n316: - **GIVEN** `MemoryStore` with `sync.RWMutex`\n317: - **WHEN** concurrent `ListExpiredSandboxes` and `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`\n318: - **THEN** `sync.RWMutex` SHALL prevent race conditions\n319: \n320: #### Scenario: runOnce called from single goroutine\n321: - **GIVEN** `runLoop` design\n322: - **WHEN** GC is running\n323: - **THEN** `runOnce` SHALL only be called from the single `runLoop` goroutine\n324: - AND no concurrent `runOnce` calls SHALL occur from GC itself\n325: \n326: ---\n327: \n328: ### Requirement: Deletion delegation\n329: \n330: The system SHALL delegate actual deletion to SandboxLifecycleManager.\n331: \n332: #### Scenario: DeleteSandbox delegation\n333: - **GIVEN** `runOnce` processing a sandbox\n334: - **WHEN** calling deletion\n335: - **THEN** `gc.manager.DeleteSandbox(ctx, sessionID)` SHALL be called\n336: - AND deletion SHALL handle both K8s CR deletion and store cleanup\n337: \n338: #### Scenario: DeleteSandbox handles K8s resources\n339: - **GIVEN** `SandboxLifecycleManager.DeleteSandbox`\n340: - **WHEN** deletion executes\n341: - **THEN** `SandboxGVR` (agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1/sandboxes) SHALL be deleted\n342: - AND `SandboxClaimGVR` SHALL be deleted if `Kind == SandboxClaimKind`\n343: \n344: ---\n345: \n346: ### Requirement: Integration with HTTPServer\n347: \n348: The system SHALL integrate GC with the HTTPServer lifecycle.\n349: \n350: #### Scenario: GC created in HTTPServer\n351: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go`\n352: - **WHEN** HTTPServer is initialized\n353: - **THEN** `NewGarbageCollector` SHALL be called with:\n354:   - `manager` = `SandboxLifecycleManager`\n355:   - `interval` = `config.GCInterval`\n356:   - `onceTimeout` = `config.GCOnceTimeout`\n357:   - `logger` = server logger\n358: \n359: #### Scenario: GC started on server start\n360: - **GIVEN** HTTPServer with GC\n361: - **WHEN** server starts\n362: - **THEN** `gc.Start()` SHALL be called\n363: \n364: #### Scenario: GC stopped on server shutdown\n365: - **GIVEN** running HTTPServer with GC\n366: - **WHEN** server shuts down\n367: - **THEN** `gc.Stop()` SHALL be called\n368: \n369: ---\n370: \n371: ### Requirement: Unit tests for GarbageCollector\n372: \n373: The system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for GC behavior.\n374: \n375: #### Scenario: TestNewGarbageCollector\n376: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n377: - **WHEN** running tests\n378: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n379:   - Constructor returns valid instance\n380:   - Custom interval and timeout are set correctly\n381: \n382: #### Scenario: TestNewGarbageCollector_DefaultInterval\n383: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n384: - **WHEN** calling `NewGarbageCollector(manager, 0, 0, logger)`\n385: - **THEN** default values SHALL be applied:\n386:   - `interval` = `GarbageCollectorInterval`\n387:   - `onceTimeout` = `2 * time.Minute`\n388: \n389: #### Scenario: TestGarbageCollector_StartStop\n390: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n391: - **WHEN** running tests\n392: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n393:   - `Start()` launches goroutine\n394:   - `Stop()` completes without hanging\n395:   - Goroutine exits cleanly\n396: \n397: #### Scenario: TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_Expired\n398: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n399: - **WHEN** running tests with expired sandbox\n400: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n401:   - Expired sandbox is deleted\n402:   - Active sandbox remains\n403: \n404: #### Scenario: TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_Inactive\n405: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n406: - **WHEN** running tests with inactive sandbox\n407: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n408:   - Inactive sandbox (LastActivity > idleTimeout ago) is deleted\n409:   - Active sandbox remains\n410: \n411: #### Scenario: TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_Limit\n412: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n413: - **WHEN** running tests with 20 expired sandboxes\n414: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n415:   - At most `GCBatchSize=16` sandboxes are deleted per cycle\n416: \n417: #### Scenario: TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_ContinueOnError\n418: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n419: - **WHEN** running tests\n420: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n421:   - All sandboxes are processed even if some deletions fail\n422: \n423: #### Scenario: TestGarbageCollector_GetStats\n424: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n425: - **WHEN** running tests\n426: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n427:   - `GetStats()` returns correct interval, timeout, idleTimeout\n428:   - `SetIdleTimeout()` updates stats correctly\n429: \n430: #### Scenario: TestGarbageCollector_ConcurrentRunOnce\n431: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n432: - **WHEN** running tests with concurrent `runOnce` calls\n433: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n434:   - Store handles concurrent access safely\n435:   - No race conditions occur\n436: \n437: ---\n438: \n439: ### Requirement: Integration tests for GC\n440: \n441: The system SHALL have integration tests verifying GC with lifecycle manager.\n442: \n443: #### Scenario: Full GC flow test\n444: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go`\n445: - **WHEN** running tests\n446: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n447:   - GC deletes expired sandboxes\n448:   - Store is updated after deletion\n449:   - Multiple GC cycles process remaining sandboxes\n450: \n451: ---\n452: \n453: ### Requirement: Error handling\n454: \n455: The system SHALL handle errors gracefully in GC operations.\n456: \n457: #### Scenario: ListExpiredSandboxes error\n458: - **GIVEN** `runOnce` execution\n459: - **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes` returns error\n460: - **THEN** `gc.logger.Error(\"failed to list expired sandboxes\", \"err\", err)` SHALL be called\n461: - AND `runOnce` SHALL return error\n462: \n463: #### Scenario: ListInactiveSandboxes error\n464: - **GIVEN** `runOnce` execution\n465: - **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes` returns error\n466: - **THEN** `gc.logger.Error(\"failed to list inactive sandboxes\", \"err\", err)` SHALL be called\n467: - AND `runOnce` SHALL return error\n468: \n469: #### Scenario: DeleteSandbox NotFound handling\n470: - **GIVEN** a sandbox already deleted\n471: - **WHEN** `DeleteSandbox` returns `NotFoundError`\n472: - **THEN** error SHALL be silently ignored\n473: - AND GC SHALL continue to next sandbox\n474: \n475: ---\n476: \n477: ### Requirement: File structure\n478: \n479: The system SHALL organize GC files correctly.\n480: \n481: #### Scenario: garbage_collector.go location\n482: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/`\n483: - **WHEN** listing files\n484: - **THEN** `garbage_collector.go` SHALL exist with:\n485:   - `GarbageCollector` struct\n486:   - `NewGarbageCollector` constructor\n487:   - `Start`, `Stop`, `runLoop`, `runOnce` methods\n488:   - `SetIdleTimeout`, `getIdleTimeout`, `GetStats` methods\n489:   - `GCBatchSize` constant\n490:   - `GarbageCollectorStats` struct\n491: \n492: #### Scenario: garbage_collector_test.go location\n493: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/`\n494: - **WHEN** listing files\n495: - **THEN** `garbage_collector_test.go` SHALL exist with unit tests\n496: \n497: #### Scenario: store.go with GC methods\n498: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/store.go`\n499: - **WHEN** reading file\n500: - **THEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes` and `ListInactiveSandboxes` SHALL be implemented\n501: \n502: #### Scenario: types.go with Store interface\n503: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go`\n504: - **WHEN** reading `Store` interface\n505: - **THEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes` and `ListInactiveSandboxes` SHALL be declared\n506: \n507: ---\n508: \n509: ### Requirement: LifecycleConfig integration\n510: \n511: The system SHALL use LifecycleConfig for GC configuration.\n512: \n513: #### Scenario: LifecycleConfig GC fields\n514: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go`\n515: - **WHEN** reading `LifecycleConfig`\n516: - **THEN** struct SHALL contain:\n517:   - `GCInterval time.Duration`\n518:   - `GCOnceTimeout time.Duration`\n519:   - `DefaultIdleTimeout time.Duration`\n520: \n521: #### Scenario: DefaultLifecycleConfig GC defaults\n522: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go`\n523: - **WHEN** calling `DefaultLifecycleConfig()`\n524: - **THEN** returned config SHALL have:\n525:   - `GCInterval` = `GarbageCollectorInterval` (2 minutes)\n526:   - `GCOnceTimeout` = `2 * time.Minute`\n527:   - `DefaultIdleTimeout` = `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout` (15 minutes)\n528: \n529: ---\n530: \n531: ## Implementation Files\n532: \n533: | File | Purpose |\n534: |------|---------|\n535: | `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` | GarbageCollector implementation with Start/Stop/runOnce |\n536: | `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go` | Unit tests for GC behavior |\n537: | `pkg/workloadmanager/store.go` | ListExpiredSandboxes/ListInactiveSandboxes implementations |\n538: | `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` | Store interface extensions, DeletionReason constants |\n539: | `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go` | determineDeletionReason, LifecycleConfig GC fields |\n540: | `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` | GarbageCollectorInterval, DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout constants |\n541: \n542: ---\n543: \n544: ## Dependencies\n545: \n546: | Package | Purpose |\n547: |---------|---------|\n548: | `context` | Context with timeout for GC cycles |\n549: | `sync` | WaitGroup, RWMutex for concurrency |\n550: | `time` | Duration, Ticker, Now for timing |\n551: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | SandboxInfo struct |\n552: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apierrors` | IsNotFound error checking |\n553: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | DeleteOptions |\n554: \n555: ---\n556: \n557: ## GC Flow Diagram\n558: \n559: ```\n560: GarbageCollector\n561: │\n562: ├── Start()\n563: │   └── wg.Add(1)\n564: │   └── go runLoop()\n565: │       ├── runOnce(ctx) [immediate]\n566: │       ├── ticker := NewTicker(interval)\n567: │       ├── select { stopCh, ticker.C }\n568: │       │   ├── ticker.C → runOnce(ctx)\n569: │       │   └── stopCh → return\n570: │       └── wg.Done()\n571: │\n572: ├── Stop()\n573: │   ├── close(stopCh)\n574: │   └── wg.Wait()\n575: │\n576: └── runOnce(ctx)\n577:     ├── ctx, cancel := WithTimeout(ctx, onceTimeout)\n578:     ├── expired := ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, now, GCBatchSize)\n579:     ├── inactiveBefore := now.Add(-idleTimeout)\n580:     ├── inactive := ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, inactiveBefore, GCBatchSize)\n581:     ├── for sb in expired + inactive:\n582:     │   ├── DeleteSandbox(ctx, sb.SessionID)\n583:     │   ├── reason := determineDeletionReason(sb, now, idleTimeout)\n584:     │   └── logger.Info(\"gc deleted sandbox\", ...)\n585:     └── return nil\n586: ```\n587: \n588: ---\n589: \n590: ## Configuration Values\n591: \n592: | Parameter | Default | Configurable | Source |\n593: |-----------|---------|--------------|--------|\n594: | `interval` | 2m | Yes | `NewGarbageCollector` param |\n595: | `onceTimeout` | 2m | Yes | `NewGarbageCollector` param |\n596: | `idleTimeout` | 15m | Yes (runtime) | `SetIdleTimeout` |\n597: | `batchSize` | 16 | No (const) | `GCBatchSize` |\n598: \n599: ---\n600: \n601: ## Deletion Reasons\n602: \n603: | Reason | Condition | Description |\n604: |--------|-----------|-------------|\n605: | `IdleTimeout` | `LastActivity + idleTimeout < now` AND `ExpiresAt > now` | Sandbox inactive for too long |\n606: | `MaxDurationReached` | `ExpiresAt < now` | Sandbox exceeded maximum TTL |\n607: | `UserRequest` | Neither above | Fallback for manual deletion |\n608: \n609: ---\n610: \n611: ## Validation Checklist\n612: \n613: - [ ] GarbageCollector struct defined with all required fields\n614: - [ ] NewGarbageCollector constructor with default fallbacks\n615: - [ ] Start() launches background goroutine\n616: - [ ] Stop() signals shutdown and waits for completion\n617: - [ ] runLoop uses ticker for periodic execution\n618: - [ ] runOnce has context timeout protection\n619: - [ ] ListExpiredSandboxes queries expired by ExpiresAt\n620: - [ ] ListInactiveSandboxes queries inactive by LastActivity\n621: - [ ] Batch limit (GCBatchSize=16) enforced per query\n622: - [ ] NotFound errors silently ignored\n623: - [ ] Deletion errors logged but don't stop cycle\n624: - [ ] determineDeletionReason categorizes deletions correctly\n625: - [ ] SetIdleTimeout runtime configuration supported\n626: - [ ] GetStats returns current configuration\n627: - [ ] idleMu protects concurrent idleTimeout access\n628: - [ ] Store interface includes GC query methods\n629: - [ ] MemoryStore implements GC query methods\n630: - [ ] LifecycleConfig includes GC parameters\n631: - [ ] DefaultLifecycleConfig provides GC defaults\n632: - [ ] Unit tests cover expired/inactive/batch scenarios\n633: - [ ] Unit tests cover concurrent safety\n634: - [ ] Integration tests verify full GC flow\n635: - [ ] Pass `go vet` with zero issues\n636: - [ ] Pass `golangci-lint` with zero issues\n637: - [ ] Unit tests pass with >80% coverage\n\n(End of file - total 637 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制\n\n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nDefine the Sandbox Garbage Collector that periodically scans and deletes expired and idle sandboxes. The GC runs as a background goroutine with configurable intervals, enforces TTL via `ExpiresAt` timestamps, handles idle timeout cleanup via `LastActivity`, and limits batch operations to prevent cluster overload.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: GarbageCollector type definition\n\nThe system SHALL define `GarbageCollector` as a background process for periodic sandbox cleanup.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-008/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775849149214,"end":1775849149251}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775849149258,"sessionID":"ses_28724eb1bffexGvVie186Cb16M","part":{"id":"prt_d78db8f360014b8EPwmnEr2RpV","messageID":"msg_d78db775400170ALOu87CV2PtB","sessionID":"ses_28724eb1bffexGvVie186Cb16M","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-8b4ac498d92d43acac7eed9818ce1aae","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-007/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-007/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器\n2: \n3: **Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** L\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Define the Kubernetes Reconciler controller that watches AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter custom resources, maintains desired state by managing sandbox pods, updates resource status conditions, and integrates with the informer framework from the generated client-go library.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Reconciler type definition\n18: \n19: The system SHALL define `Reconciler` as a Kubernetes controller for reconciling AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Reconciler struct definition\n22: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler.go`\n23: - **WHEN** reading the `Reconciler` struct\n24: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n25:   - `client clientset.Interface` for typed Kubernetes API access (from `client-go/clientset/versioned`)\n26:   - `kubeClient kubernetes.Interface` for core Kubernetes API\n27:   - `store Store` for sandbox state persistence\n28:   - `logger Logger` for structured logging\n29:   - `namespace string` for default namespace\n30:   - `scheme *runtime.Scheme` for encoding/decoding resources\n31:   - `recorder record.EventRecorder` for Kubernetes events\n32: \n33: #### Scenario: NewReconciler constructor\n34: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler.go`\n35: - **WHEN** calling `NewReconciler(client clientset.Interface, kubeClient kubernetes.Interface, store Store, logger Logger, namespace string, scheme *runtime.Scheme, recorder record.EventRecorder)`\n36: - **THEN** it SHALL return `*Reconciler` with all fields initialized\n37: \n38: ---\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: Informer integration\n41: \n42: The system SHALL use informers from client-go library to watch custom resources.\n43: \n44: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime informer setup\n45: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler.go`\n46: - **WHEN** initializing the reconciler\n47: - **THEN** `SharedInformerFactory` from `client-go/informers/externalversions` SHALL be used\n48: - AND `f.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Informer()` SHALL be accessed for AgentRuntime watching\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter informer setup\n51: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler.go`\n52: - **WHEN** initializing the reconciler\n53: - **THEN** `SharedInformerFactory.Runtime().V1alpha1().CodeInterpreters().Informer()` SHALL be accessed for CodeInterpreter watching\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: Informer event handlers\n56: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter informers\n57: - **WHEN** setting up event handlers\n58: - **THEN** `AddFunc`, `UpdateFunc`, `DeleteFunc` SHALL be registered on each informer\n59: - AND each handler SHALL call `Reconciler.Reconcile(ctx, key)` with the resource key\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: Informer Start\n62: - **GIVEN** a configured `SharedInformerFactory`\n63: - **WHEN** calling `factory.Start(stopCh)`\n64: - **THEN** all informers SHALL begin watching resources\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: WaitForCacheSync\n67: - **GIVEN** a started informer factory\n68: - **WHEN** calling `factory.WaitForCacheSync(stopCh)`\n69: - **THEN** it SHALL return `map[reflect.Type]bool` indicating sync status\n70: - AND all types SHALL be `true` before reconciliation begins\n71: \n72: ---\n73: \n74: ### Requirement: Reconcile method\n75: \n76: The system SHALL implement the Reconcile method to process resource changes.\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: Reconcile method signature\n79: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler.go`\n80: - **WHEN** reading the `Reconcile` method\n81: - **THEN** it SHALL have signature `Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req reconcile.Request) (reconcile.Result, error)`\n82: - AND SHALL implement `reconcile.Reconciler` interface from `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime`\n83: \n84: #### Scenario: Reconcile parses request key\n85: - **GIVEN** a `reconcile.Request` with `Namespace=\"default\"` and `Name=\"my-runtime\"`\n86: - **WHEN** processing the reconcile request\n87: - **THEN** the reconciler SHALL use `req.Namespace` and `req.Name` to fetch the resource\n88: \n89: #### Scenario: Reconcile fetches AgentRuntime\n90: - **GIVEN** a reconcile request for an AgentRuntime\n91: - **WHEN** processing the request\n92: - **THEN** `client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Get(ctx, name, metav1.GetOptions{})` SHALL be called\n93: - AND the returned `AgentRuntime` SHALL be used for reconciliation\n94: \n95: #### Scenario: Reconcile fetches CodeInterpreter\n96: - **GIVEN** a reconcile request for a CodeInterpreter\n97: - **WHEN** processing the request\n98: - **THEN** `client.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Get(ctx, name, metav1.GetOptions{})` SHALL be called\n99: - AND the returned `CodeInterpreter` SHALL be used for reconciliation\n100: \n101: #### Scenario: Reconcile handles not found\n102: - **GIVEN** a reconcile request for a deleted resource\n103: - **WHEN** `Get` returns `IsNotFound` error\n104: - **THEN** reconciliation SHALL return `reconcile.Result{}` with no error\n105: - AND cleanup logic SHALL be triggered if needed\n106: \n107: ---\n108: \n109: ### Requirement: Status update\n110: \n111: The system SHALL update status conditions on AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources.\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: Update AgentRuntime status\n114: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with updated conditions\n115: - **WHEN** calling status update\n116: - **THEN** `client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).UpdateStatus(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.UpdateOptions{})` SHALL be called\n117: \n118: #### Scenario: Update CodeInterpreter status\n119: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with updated conditions\n120: - **WHEN** calling status update\n121: - **THEN** `client.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace).UpdateStatus(ctx, codeInterpreter, metav1.UpdateOptions{})` SHALL be called\n122: \n123: #### Scenario: Set Ready condition\n124: - **GIVEN** a runtime that is ready to serve\n125: - **WHEN** updating status\n126: - **THEN** condition `ConditionTypeReady` SHALL be set with:\n127:   - `Type: \"Ready\"`\n128:   - `Status: metav1.ConditionTrue`\n129:   - `Reason: ConditionReasonRunning`\n130:   - `Message: \"Runtime is ready\"`\n131: \n132: #### Scenario: Set Progressing condition\n133: - **GIVEN** a runtime being created or updated\n134: - **WHEN** updating status\n135: - **THEN** condition `ConditionTypeProgressing` SHALL be set with:\n136:   - `Type: \"Progressing\"`\n137:   - `Status: metav1.ConditionTrue`\n138:   - `Reason: ConditionReasonCreating` or `ConditionReasonUpdating`\n139: \n140: #### Scenario: Set Degraded condition\n141: - **GIVEN** a runtime with errors\n142: - **WHEN** updating status\n143: - **THEN** condition `ConditionTypeDegraded` SHALL be set with:\n144:   - `Type: \"Degraded\"`\n145:   - `Status: metav1.ConditionTrue`\n146:   - `Reason: ConditionReasonError`\n147: \n148: #### Scenario: Set Available condition\n149: - **GIVEN** a runtime with active pods\n150: - **WHEN** updating status\n151: - **THEN** condition `ConditionTypeAvailable` SHALL be set with:\n152:   - `Type: \"Available\"`\n153:   - `Status: metav1.ConditionTrue`\n154:   - `Reason: ConditionReasonRunning`\n155: \n156: ---\n157: \n158: ### Requirement: Lister usage\n159: \n160: The system SHALL use listers from client-go for efficient resource lookup.\n161: \n162: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime lister\n163: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler.go`\n164: - **WHEN** using the AgentRuntime lister\n165: - **THEN** `AgentRuntimeLister` from `client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1` SHALL be used\n166: - AND `lister.AgentRuntimes(namespace).Get(name)` SHALL return cached AgentRuntime\n167: \n168: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter lister\n169: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler.go`\n170: - **WHEN** using the CodeInterpreter lister\n171: - **THEN** `CodeInterpreterLister` from `client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1` SHALL be used\n172: - AND `lister.CodeInterpreters(namespace).Get(name)` SHALL return cached CodeInterpreter\n173: \n174: #### Scenario: Pod lister for sandbox lookup\n175: - **GIVEN** a reconciler looking for sandbox pods\n176: - **WHEN** searching for pods owned by a runtime\n177: - **THEN** `corev1listers.PodLister` SHALL be used\n178: - AND `lister.Pods(namespace).List(selector)` SHALL return pods matching label selector\n179: \n180: ---\n181: \n182: ### Requirement: Warm pool reconciler for CodeInterpreter\n183: \n184: The system SHALL maintain warm pool pods for CodeInterpreter resources.\n185: \n186: #### Scenario: Warm pool size check\n187: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `WarmPoolSize=5`\n188: - **WHEN** reconciling\n189: - **THEN** the reconciler SHALL count existing warm pool pods\n190: - AND pods with annotation `AnnotationKeyWarmPoolMember=\"true\"` SHALL be counted\n191: \n192: #### Scenario: Create warm pool pod\n193: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `WarmPoolSize > currentWarmPoolCount`\n194: - **WHEN** reconciling\n195: - **THEN** new warm pool pods SHALL be created\n196: - AND annotation `AnnotationKeyWarmPoolMember` SHALL be set to `\"true\"`\n197: - AND label `LabelKeyOwnerRuntime` SHALL be set to CodeInterpreter name\n198: - AND label `LabelKeyOwnerKind` SHALL be set to `\"CodeInterpreter\"`\n199: \n200: #### Scenario: Delete excess warm pool pods\n201: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `WarmPoolSize < currentWarmPoolCount`\n202: - **WHEN** reconciling\n203: - **THEN** excess warm pool pods SHALL be deleted\n204: - AND pods SHALL be selected based on oldest creation timestamp\n205: \n206: #### Scenario: Warm pool pod spec\n207: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter template\n208: - **WHEN** creating warm pool pod\n209: - **THEN** pod spec SHALL be derived from `CodeInterpreter.Spec.Template`\n210: - AND `Image` SHALL be from `Template.Image`\n211: - AND `RuntimeClassName` SHALL be from `Template.RuntimeClassName` if set\n212: \n213: ---\n214: \n215: ### Requirement: Event recording\n216: \n217: The system SHALL record Kubernetes events for resource lifecycle.\n218: \n219: #### Scenario: Record created event\n220: - **GIVEN** a newly created AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter\n221: - **WHEN** reconciliation succeeds\n222: - **THEN** `recorder.Event(object, \"Normal\", \"Created\", \"Runtime created successfully\")` SHALL be called\n223: \n224: #### Scenario: Record Updated event\n225: - **GIVEN** an updated AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter\n226: - **WHEN** reconciliation succeeds\n227: - **THEN** `recorder.Event(object, \"Normal\", \"Updated\", \"Runtime updated successfully\")` SHALL be called\n228: \n229: #### Scenario: Record Error event\n230: - **GIVEN** a reconciliation error\n231: - **WHEN** error occurs\n232: - **THEN** `recorder.Event(object, \"Warning\", \"Error\", errorMessage)` SHALL be called\n233: \n234: #### Scenario: Record SessionStarted event\n235: - **GIVEN** a runtime with active session\n236: - **WHEN** session starts\n237: - **THEN** `recorder.Event(object, \"Normal\", \"SessionStarted\", \"Session started\")` SHALL be called\n238: \n239: #### Scenario: Record SessionEnded event\n240: - **GIVEN** a runtime with ended session\n241: - **WHEN** session ends\n242: - **THEN** `recorder.Event(object, \"Normal\", \"SessionEnded\", \"Session ended: <reason>\")` SHALL be called\n243: \n244: ---\n245: \n246: ### Requirement: Reconcile loop control\n247: \n248: The system SHALL control reconcile loop timing and retries.\n249: \n250: #### Scenario: Requeue on error\n251: - **GIVEN** a reconciliation that returns error\n252: - **WHEN** processing result\n253: - **THEN** `reconcile.Result{Requeue: true, RequeueAfter: ReconcileErrorRetryInterval}` SHALL be returned\n254: - AND default retry interval SHALL be `1 * time.Minute`\n255: \n256: #### Scenario: Requeue for periodic check\n257: - **GIVEN** a successful reconciliation\n258: - **WHEN** periodic status check is needed\n259: - **THEN** `reconcile.Result{RequeueAfter: ReconcilePeriodicInterval}` SHALL be returned\n260: - AND default periodic interval SHALL be `5 * time.Minute`\n261: \n262: #### Scenario: No requeue on completion\n263: - **GIVEN** a resource that is fully reconciled\n264: - **WHEN** no further action is needed\n265: - **THEN** `reconcile.Result{}` SHALL be returned\n266: \n267: ---\n268: \n269: ### Requirement: Controller setup\n270: \n271: The system SHALL provide controller setup and management functions.\n272: \n273: #### Scenario: ControllerManager setup\n274: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/controller.go`\n275: - **WHEN** reading the setup\n276: - **THEN** `SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager)` SHALL be implemented\n277: - AND SHALL use `ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).For(&runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{}).Complete(r)` pattern\n278: \n279: #### Scenario: Watches setup for AgentRuntime\n280: - **GIVEN** controller setup for AgentRuntime\n281: - **WHEN** configuring watches\n282: - **THEN** `For(&runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{})` SHALL be called\n283: - AND `Owns(&corev1.Pod{})` SHALL be called for owned pods\n284: \n285: #### Scenario: Watches setup for CodeInterpreter\n286: - **GIVEN** controller setup for CodeInterpreter\n287: - **WHEN** configuring watches\n288: - **THEN** `For(&runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter{})` SHALL be called\n289: - AND `Owns(&corev1.Pod{})` SHALL be called for owned pods\n290: \n291: ---\n292: \n293: ### Requirement: Resource deletion handling\n294: \n295: The system SHALL handle resource deletion gracefully.\n296: \n297: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime deletion\n298: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime being deleted\n299: - **WHEN** reconciling with deletion timestamp set\n300: - **THEN** all sandbox pods owned by the runtime SHALL be deleted\n301: - AND status SHALL be updated with `ConditionReasonDeleting`\n302: \n303: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter deletion\n304: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter being deleted\n305: - **WHEN** reconciling with deletion timestamp set\n306: - **THEN** all sandbox pods and warm pool pods SHALL be deleted\n307: - AND status SHALL be updated with `ConditionReasonDeleting`\n308: \n309: #### Scenario: Deletion cleanup\n310: - **GIVEN** a deleted runtime\n311: - **WHEN** all pods are deleted\n312: - **THEN** store entries SHALL be removed for associated sandboxes\n313: - AND finalizer SHALL be removed if present\n314: \n315: ---\n316: \n317: ### Requirement: Finalizer handling\n318: \n319: The system SHALL use finalizers for cleanup before deletion.\n320: \n321: #### Scenario: Add finalizer on creation\n322: - **GIVEN** a newly created AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter\n323: - **WHEN** reconciling for the first time\n324: - **THEN** finalizer `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/finalizer` SHALL be added to metadata.finalizers\n325: \n326: #### Scenario: Process finalizer on deletion\n327: - **GIVEN** a runtime with deletion timestamp and finalizer present\n328: - **WHEN** reconciling\n329: - **THEN** cleanup logic SHALL run first\n330: - AND finalizer SHALL be removed after cleanup succeeds\n331: \n332: #### Scenario: Finalizer removal error handling\n333: - **GIVEN** cleanup that fails\n334: - **WHEN** processing finalizer\n335: - **THEN** finalizer SHALL NOT be removed\n336: - AND reconciliation SHALL requeue with error\n337: \n338: ---\n339: \n340: ### Requirement: Scheme registration\n341: \n342: The system SHALL register custom resource types in the scheme.\n343: \n344: #### Scenario: Scheme registration\n345: - **GIVEN** `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go` and `groupversion_info.go`\n346: - **WHEN** setting up the reconciler\n347: - **THEN** `runtimev1alpha1.AddToScheme(scheme)` SHALL be called\n348: - AND `corev1.AddToScheme(scheme)` SHALL be called for Pod types\n349: \n350: #### Scenario: Scheme from client-go\n351: - **GIVEN** `client-go/clientset/versioned/scheme`\n352: - **WHEN** using the scheme\n353: - **THEN** `Scheme` and `Codecs` SHALL be available from `register.go`\n354: - AND types SHALL be registered for `runtime/v1alpha1`\n355: \n356: ---\n357: \n358: ### Requirement: Concurrent reconciliation safety\n359: \n360: The system SHALL handle concurrent reconciliations safely.\n361: \n362: #### Scenario: Same resource concurrent reconcile\n363: - **GIVEN** two reconcile requests for the same resource\n364: - **WHEN** both execute concurrently\n365: - **THEN** only one SHALL proceed with status update\n366: - AND optimistic locking via `ResourceVersion` SHALL prevent conflicts\n367: \n368: #### Scenario: Conflict retry\n369: - **GIVEN** a status update that returns conflict error\n370: - **WHEN** retrying\n371: - **THEN** the resource SHALL be re-fetched\n372: - AND reconciliation SHALL retry with fresh data\n373: \n374: ---\n375: \n376: ### Requirement: Logger integration\n377: \n378: The system SHALL use structured logging for reconciliation.\n379: \n380: #### Scenario: Reconcile start logging\n381: - **GIVEN** a reconcile request\n382: - **WHEN** starting reconciliation\n383: - **THEN** `logger.Info(\"Reconciling\", \"kind\", kind, \"namespace\", namespace, \"name\", name)` SHALL be called\n384: \n385: #### Scenario: Reconcile error logging\n386: - **GIVEN** a reconciliation error\n387: - **WHEN** error occurs\n388: - **THEN** `logger.Error(err, \"Reconcile failed\", \"kind\", kind, \"namespace\", namespace, \"name\", name)` SHALL be called\n389: \n390: #### Scenario: Reconcile success logging\n391: - **GIVEN** a successful reconciliation\n392: - **WHEN** completing\n393: - **THEN** `logger.Info(\"Reconcile completed\", \"kind\", kind, \"namespace\", namespace, \"name\", name)` SHALL be called\n394: \n395: ---\n396: \n397: ### Requirement: Unit tests for Reconciler\n398: \n399: The system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for the reconciler.\n400: \n401: #### Scenario: Reconciler creation test\n402: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler_test.go`\n403: - **WHEN** running tests\n404: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n405:   - NewReconciler returns valid instance\n406:   - All fields are properly initialized\n407: \n408: #### Scenario: Reconcile AgentRuntime test\n409: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler_test.go`\n410: - **WHEN** running tests\n411: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n412:   - AgentRuntime fetch succeeds\n413:   - Status updates are called correctly\n414:   - Conditions are set properly\n415: \n416: #### Scenario: Reconcile CodeInterpreter test\n417: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler_test.go`\n418: - **WHEN** running tests\n419: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n420:   - CodeInterpreter fetch succeeds\n421:   - Warm pool pods are created/deleted as needed\n422:   - Status updates are called correctly\n423: \n424: #### Scenario: Not found handling test\n425: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler_test.go`\n426: - **WHEN** running tests\n427: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n428:   - NotFound error returns empty result\n429:   - Cleanup is triggered for deleted resources\n430: \n431: #### Scenario: Status conflict test\n432: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler_test.go`\n433: - **WHEN** running tests\n434: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n435:   - Conflict error triggers retry\n436:   - Resource is re-fetched on conflict\n437: \n438: ---\n439: \n440: ### Requirement: Integration tests for Reconciler\n441: \n442: The system SHALL have integration tests with fake clients.\n443: \n444: #### Scenario: Full reconciliation flow test\n445: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go`\n446: - **WHEN** running tests\n447: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n448:   - Informer factory starts correctly\n449:   - WaitForCacheSync returns true\n450:   - Reconcile is triggered on resource changes\n451:   - Status is updated correctly\n452: \n453: #### Scenario: Warm pool integration test\n454: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go`\n455: - **WHEN** running tests\n456: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n457:   - Warm pool pods are created to match WarmPoolSize\n458:   - Warm pool pods have correct labels and annotations\n459:   - Excess pods are deleted when WarmPoolSize decreases\n460: \n461: #### Scenario: Deletion integration test\n462: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go`\n463: - **WHEN** running tests\n464: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n465:   - All pods are deleted when runtime is deleted\n466:   - Finalizer is removed after cleanup\n467:   - Store entries are removed\n468: \n469: ---\n470: \n471: ### Requirement: Fake client usage in tests\n472: \n473: The system SHALL use fake clients from client-go library in tests.\n474: \n475: #### Scenario: Fake clientset creation\n476: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler_test.go`\n477: - **WHEN** setting up tests\n478: - **THEN** `fake.NewSimpleClientset(objects)` from `client-go/clientset/versioned/fake` SHALL be used\n479: \n480: #### Scenario: Fake typed client\n481: - **GIVEN** test setup\n482: - **WHEN** creating fake typed client\n483: - **THEN** `fake_runtime_client.go`, `fake_agentruntime.go`, `fake_codeinterpreter.go` SHALL be available\n484: \n485: #### Scenario: Fake informer factory\n486: - **GIVEN** test setup\n487: - **WHEN** creating fake informer factory\n488: - **THEN** `informers/externalversions/factory.go` SHALL work with fake client\n489: \n490: ---\n491: \n492: ### Requirement: Constants and defaults\n493: \n494: The system SHALL define reconciler constants and defaults.\n495: \n496: #### Scenario: Reconcile intervals\n497: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n498: - **WHEN** reading constants\n499: - **THEN** `ReconcileErrorRetryInterval` SHALL be `1 * time.Minute`\n500: - AND `ReconcilePeriodicInterval` SHALL be `5 * time.Minute`\n501: \n502: #### Scenario: Finalizer name\n503: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n504: - **WHEN** reading constants\n505: - **THEN** `FinalizerName` SHALL be `\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/finalizer\"`\n506: \n507: ---\n508: \n509: ### Requirement: Directory structure\n510: \n511: The system SHALL organize reconciler files correctly.\n512: \n513: #### Scenario: Reconciler file location\n514: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/`\n515: - **WHEN** listing files\n516: - **THEN** `reconciler.go` SHALL exist with `Reconciler` implementation\n517: \n518: #### Scenario: Reconciler test file location\n519: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/`\n520: - **WHEN** listing files\n521: - **THEN** `reconciler_test.go` SHALL exist with unit tests\n522: \n523: #### Scenario: Controller setup file location\n524: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/`\n525: - **WHEN** listing files\n526: - **THEN** `controller.go` SHALL exist with controller setup functions\n527: \n528: ---\n529: \n530: ## Implementation Files\n531: \n532: | File | Purpose |\n533: |------|---------|\n534: | `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler.go` | Reconciler implementation |\n535: | `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler_test.go` | Reconciler unit tests |\n536: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller.go` | Controller setup and manager integration |\n537: | `pkg/workloadmanager/controller_test.go` | Controller setup tests |\n538: \n539: ---\n540: \n541: ## Dependencies\n542: \n543: | Package | Purpose |\n544: |---------|---------|\n545: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned` | Typed client for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter |\n546: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/informers/externalversions` | SharedInformerFactory |\n547: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1` | AgentRuntimeLister, CodeInterpreterLister |\n548: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | Reconciler interface, ControllerManager |\n549: | `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes` | Core Kubernetes API client |\n550: | `k8s.io/client-go/tools/record` | EventRecorder |\n551: | `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | Pod types |\n552: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime` | Scheme |\n553: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | Conditions, ObjectMeta |\n554: \n555: ---\n556: \n557: ## Client-go Integration Points\n558: \n559: | Component | Source File | Usage |\n560: |-----------|-------------|-------|\n561: | Typed client | `clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/` | Get, Update, UpdateStatus, Delete |\n562: | Informer factory | `informers/externalversions/factory.go` | Start, WaitForCacheSync |\n563: | AgentRuntime informer | `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | Informer(), Lister() |\n564: | CodeInterpreter informer | `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | Informer(), Lister() |\n565: | AgentRuntime lister | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go` | List, Get |\n566: | CodeInterpreter lister | `listers/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` | List, Get |\n567: | Fake clientset | `clientset/versioned/fake/` | Unit test mock |\n568: | Scheme | `clientset/versioned/scheme/` | Resource encoding |\n569: \n570: ---\n571: \n572: ## Reconcile Result Values\n573: \n574: | Result | Requeue | RequeueAfter | Use Case |\n575: |--------|---------|--------------|----------|\n576: | `{}` | false | 0 | Completed, no further action |\n577: | `{Requeue: true}` | true | 0 | Immediate retry |\n578: | `{RequeueAfter: 1m}` | true | 1m | Error retry with delay |\n579: | `{RequeueAfter: 5m}` | true | 5m | Periodic check |\n580: \n581: ---\n582: \n583: ## Condition Types and Reasons\n584: \n585: | Condition Type | Reason | Status | Description |\n586: |----------------|--------|--------|-------------|\n587: | `Ready` | `Running` | True | Runtime ready to serve |\n588: | `Ready` | `Creating` | False | Runtime being created |\n589: | `Progressing` | `Creating` | True | Creation in progress |\n590: | `Progressing` | `Updating` | True | Update in progress |\n591: | `Available` | `Running` | True | Runtime available |\n592: | `Degraded` | `Error` | True | Runtime has errors |\n593: | `SessionActive` | `SessionStarted` | True | Active session |\n594: | `SessionActive` | `SessionEnded` | False | No active session |\n595: \n596: ---\n597: \n598: ## Event Types\n599: \n600: | Event Type | Reason | Message Pattern |\n601: |------------|--------|-----------------|\n602: | Normal | Created | \"Runtime created successfully\" |\n603: | Normal | Updated | \"Runtime updated successfully\" |\n604: | Normal | SessionStarted | \"Session started\" |\n605: | Normal | SessionEnded | \"Session ended: <reason>\" |\n606: | Warning | Error | \"<error message>\" |\n607: \n608: ---\n609: \n610: ## Warm Pool Labels and Annotations\n611: \n612: | Key | Value | Purpose |\n613: |-----|-------|---------|\n614: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/warm-pool-member` | `\"true\"` | Mark pod as warm pool member |\n615: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/owner-runtime` | `<name>` | Reference to CodeInterpreter |\n616: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/owner-kind` | `\"CodeInterpreter\"` | Owner kind |\n617: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/sandbox-type` | `\"code-interpreter\"` | Sandbox type |\n618: \n619: ---\n620: \n621: ## Validation Checklist\n622: \n623: - [ ] Reconciler struct defined with all required fields\n624: - [ ] NewReconciler constructor initializes all fields\n625: - [ ] Reconcile method implements reconcile.Reconciler interface\n626: - [ ] AgentRuntime informer registered with event handlers\n627: - [ ] CodeInterpreter informer registered with event handlers\n628: - [ ] WaitForCacheSync called before reconciliation\n629: - [ ] Status updates use UpdateStatus method\n630: - [ ] Conditions set with proper Type, Status, Reason, Message\n631: - [ ] AgentRuntimeLister used for cached lookups\n632: - [ ] CodeInterpreterLister used for cached lookups\n633: - [ ] Pod lister used for sandbox pod lookup\n634: - [ ] Warm pool pods created/deleted to match WarmPoolSize\n635: - [ ] Events recorded for lifecycle changes\n636: - [ ] Requeue intervals configured appropriately\n637: - [ ] ControllerManager setup implemented\n638: - [ ] Watches configured for CRDs and Pods\n639: - [ ] Finalizer added on creation\n640: - [ ] Finalizer processed on deletion\n641: - [ ] Scheme registered with runtime/v1alpha1 and corev1\n642: - [ ] Conflict retry handles optimistic locking\n643: - [ ] Logger integration with structured logging\n644: - [ ] Fake clientset used in unit tests\n645: - [ ] Pass `go vet` with zero issues\n646: - [ ] Pass `golangci-lint` with zero issues\n647: - [ ] Unit tests pass with >80% coverage\n648: - [ ] Integration tests pass\n\n(End of file - total 648 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器\n\n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** L\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nDefine the Kubernetes Reconciler controller that watches AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter custom resources, maintains desired state by managing sandbox pods, updates resource status conditions, and integrates with the informer framework from the generated client-go library.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: Reconciler type definition\n\nThe system SHALL define `Reconciler` as a Kubernetes controller for reconciling AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-007/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775849149216,"end":1775849149254}}}}
