{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775849154398,"sessionID":"ses_28724eb1bffexGvVie186Cb16M","part":{"id":"prt_d78dba75a001ad6IExdclBcWtk","messageID":"msg_d78db938b001Pidhi1LsRXb5uB","sessionID":"ses_28724eb1bffexGvVie186Cb16M","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775849324149,"sessionID":"ses_28724eb1bffexGvVie186Cb16M","part":{"id":"prt_d78de3dfa001A8CFZrkMhKR2HJ","messageID":"msg_d78db938b001Pidhi1LsRXb5uB","sessionID":"ses_28724eb1bffexGvVie186Cb16M","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-7687381cb24f49aa946cc505542628ac","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-009/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Spec: AR-009 — Router HTTP 反向代理核心\n\n**Module:** `pkg/router`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nDefine the HTTP reverse proxy core for the AgentCube Router component. This provides session-aware routing that resolves session IDs from request headers, creates sandboxes via Workload Manager, forwards HTTP requests to sandbox pod endpoints using `httputil.ReverseProxy`, generates RS256-signed JWT tokens, updates session activity timestamps, and limits concurrent requests via semaphore middleware.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: Server type definition\n\nThe system SHALL define `Server` as an HTTP server with Gin engine for reverse proxy routing.\n\n#### Scenario: Server struct definition\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server.go`\n- **WHEN** reading the `Server` struct\n- **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n  - `config *Config` for server configuration\n  - `engine *gin.Engine` for Gin HTTP framework\n  - `httpServer *http.Server` for underlying HTTP server\n  - `sessionManager SessionManager` for session resolution\n  - `store Store` for session state persistence\n  - `jwtManager JWTManager` for JWT token generation\n  - `transport *http.Transport` for HTTP transport sharing\n  - `logger Logger` for structured logging\n\n#### Scenario: Config struct definition\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/config.go`\n- **WHEN** reading the `Config` struct\n- **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n  - `Port int` for listening port (default 8080)\n  - `EnableTLS bool` for TLS enablement\n  - `TLSCert string` for TLS certificate file path\n  - `TLSKey string` for TLS private key file path\n  - `MaxConcurrentRequests int` for concurrency limit\n  - `Debug bool` for debug mode\n\n#### Scenario: NewServer constructor\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server.go`\n- **WHEN** calling `NewServer(config *Config, sessionManager SessionManager, store Store, jwtManager JWTManager, logger Logger)`\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `*Server` with:\n  - `engine` initialized with `gin.New()`\n  - `gin.SetMode(gin.ReleaseMode)` if `config.Debug == false`\n  - `gin.SetMode(gin.DebugMode)` if `config.Debug == true`\n  - `transport` initialized with shared HTTP transport\n  - `httpServer` initialized with h2c configuration\n\n#### Scenario: DefaultConfig\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/config.go`\n- **WHEN** calling `DefaultConfig()`\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `*Config` with:\n  - `Port` = `8080`\n  - `EnableTLS` = `false`\n  - `MaxConcurrentRequests` = `1000`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Server lifecycle\n\nThe system SHALL provide Start/Stop lifecycle methods with graceful shutdown.\n\n#### Scenario: Start without TLS\n- **GIVEN** a `Server` with `config.EnableTLS == false`\n- **WHEN** calling `server.Start(ctx)`\n- **THEN** `httpServer.ListenAndServe()` SHALL be called\n- AND h2c server SHALL handle HTTP/2 without TLS\n\n#### Scenario: Start with TLS\n- **GIVEN** a `Server` with `config.EnableTLS == true`\n- **WHEN** calling `server.Start(ctx)`\n- **THEN** `httpServer.ListenAndServeTLS(config.TLSCert, config.TLSKey)` SHALL be called\n- AND error SHALL be returned if cert/key files are missing\n\n#### Scenario: Graceful shutdown\n- **GIVEN** a running `Server`\n- **WHEN** context is cancelled\n- **THEN** `httpServer.Shutdown(shutdownCtx)` SHALL be called\n- AND shutdown deadline SHALL be `10s`\n- AND server SHALL stop accepting new connections\n- AND existing connections SHALL complete\n\n#### Scenario: Server timeouts\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server.go`\n- **WHEN** initializing `httpServer`\n- **THEN** timeouts SHALL be configured:\n  - `ReadTimeout` = `30s`\n  - `IdleTimeout` = `90s`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Route registration\n\nThe system SHALL register routes for health endpoints and invocation paths.\n\n#### Scenario: Health routes\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server.go`\n- **WHEN** registering routes\n- **THEN** `/health/live` SHALL be registered with `handleHealthLive`\n- AND `/health/ready` SHALL be registered with `handleHealthReady`\n\n#### Scenario: Invocation routes\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server.go`\n- **WHEN** registering routes\n- **THEN** `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` SHALL be registered\n- AND `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` SHALL be registered\n- AND both `GET` and `POST` methods SHALL be supported\n\n#### Scenario: Middleware chain\n- **GIVEN** route registration\n- **WHEN** applying middleware\n- **THEN** `concurrencyLimitMiddleware` SHALL be applied globally\n- AND `loggingMiddleware` SHALL be applied for request logging\n- AND `recoveryMiddleware` SHALL be applied for panic recovery\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: SessionManager interface\n\nThe system SHALL define `SessionManager` interface for session resolution and sandbox creation.\n\n#### Scenario: SessionManager interface definition\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n- **WHEN** reading the `SessionManager` interface\n- **THEN** interface SHALL include:\n  - `GetSandboxBySession(ctx context.Context, sessionID, namespace, name, kind string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n\n#### Scenario: manager struct definition\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n- **WHEN** reading the `manager` struct\n- **THEN** struct SHALL contain:\n  - `storeClient Store` for session lookup\n  - `workloadMgrAddr string` for Workload Manager URL\n  - `httpClient *http.Client` for sandbox creation requests\n  - `logger Logger` for structured logging\n\n#### Scenario: NewSessionManager constructor\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n- **WHEN** calling `NewSessionManager(store Store, logger Logger)`\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `*manager` with:\n  - `workloadMgrAddr` from `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable\n  - startup SHALL fail if `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` is not set\n  - `httpClient` with `Timeout=2m`, `MaxIdleConnsPerHost=100`\n\n#### Scenario: HTTP client configuration\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n- **WHEN** initializing `httpClient`\n- **THEN** HTTP2 SHALL be configured with:\n  - `ReadIdleTimeout` = `30s`\n  - `PingTimeout` = `15s`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Session resolution\n\nThe system SHALL resolve sessions by ID and create new sandboxes when missing.\n\n#### Scenario: GetSandboxBySession with existing session\n- **GIVEN** a session ID that exists in store\n- **WHEN** calling `GetSandboxBySession(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind)`\n- **THEN** `store.GetSession(ctx, sessionID)` SHALL be called\n- AND `*SandboxInfo` SHALL be returned if found\n\n#### Scenario: GetSandboxBySession creates new sandbox\n- **GIVEN** a session ID that does NOT exist in store\n- **WHEN** calling `GetSandboxBySession(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind)`\n- **THEN** `createSandbox(ctx, namespace, name, kind)` SHALL be called\n- AND POST request SHALL be sent to Workload Manager\n\n#### Scenario: createSandbox POST request\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n- **WHEN** calling `createSandbox(ctx, namespace, name, kind)`\n- **THEN** POST SHALL be sent to:\n  - `/v1/agent-runtime` for `AgentRuntimeKind`\n  - `/v1/code-interpreter` for `CodeInterpreterKind`\n- AND request body SHALL be `CreateSandboxRequest`\n\n#### Scenario: createSandbox with K8s SA token\n- **GIVEN** in-cluster deployment\n- **WHEN** sending POST to Workload Manager\n- **THEN** `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` SHALL be read\n- AND token SHALL be set as `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header\n\n#### Scenario: createSandbox namespace\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n- **WHEN** creating sandbox\n- **THEN** `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` environment variable SHALL be read for target namespace\n- AND default namespace SHALL be `\"default\"` if not set\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Reverse proxy implementation\n\nThe system SHALL implement reverse proxy with custom Director and error handling.\n\n#### Scenario: ReverseProxy struct definition\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n- **WHEN** reading the implementation\n- **THEN** `httputil.NewSingleHostReverseProxy` SHALL be used as base\n- AND custom `Director` function SHALL be set\n- AND custom `ModifyResponse` function SHALL be set\n- AND custom `ErrorHandler` function SHALL be set\n\n#### Scenario: Director path normalization\n- **GIVEN** a request with path `/api/run`\n- **WHEN** Director processes the request\n- **THEN** leading slash SHALL be prefixed if missing: `//api/run` → `/api/run`\n- AND path SHALL match entry point from `SandboxInfo.EntryPoints`\n\n#### Scenario: Director forwarding headers\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n- **WHEN** Director processes request\n- **THEN** `req.Host` SHALL be set to target host\n- AND `X-Forwarded-For` SHALL be set with client IP\n- AND `X-Real-IP` SHALL be set with client IP\n\n#### Scenario: Director JWT injection\n- **GIVEN** a proxied request\n- **WHEN** Director processes request\n- **THEN** JWT token SHALL be generated by `jwtManager`\n- AND `Authorization: Bearer <jwt>` SHALL be added to request headers\n\n#### Scenario: ModifyResponse session header injection\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go`\n- **WHEN** ModifyResponse processes response\n- **THEN** `x-agentcube-session-id` header SHALL be added to response\n- AND value SHALL be the resolved session ID\n\n#### Scenario: ErrorHandler connection refused\n- **GIVEN** proxy error with connection refused\n- **WHEN** ErrorHandler processes error\n- **THEN** HTTP `502` SHALL be returned\n- AND error code SHALL be `sandbox unreachable`\n\n#### Scenario: ErrorHandler timeout\n- **GIVEN** proxy error with timeout\n- **WHEN** ErrorHandler processes error\n- **THEN** HTTP `504` SHALL be returned\n- AND error code SHALL be `sandbox timeout`\n\n#### Scenario: Entry point matching\n- **GIVEN** `SandboxInfo.EntryPoints` with multiple entry points\n- **WHEN** selecting entry point\n- **THEN** first entry point with matching path prefix SHALL be used\n- AND `Endpoint` SHALL be the proxy target URL\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: JWT Manager\n\nThe system SHALL implement JWT token generation with RSA signing and K8s Secret persistence.\n\n#### Scenario: JWTManager interface definition\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n- **WHEN** reading the `JWTManager` interface\n- **THEN** interface SHALL include:\n  - `GenerateToken(ctx context.Context, kind, name, namespace string) (string, error)`\n  - `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx context.Context) error`\n\n#### Scenario: jwtManager struct definition\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n- **WHEN** reading the `jwtManager` struct\n- **THEN** struct SHALL contain:\n  - `privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey` for RSA private key\n  - `publicKey *rsa.PublicKey` for RSA public key\n  - `kubeClient kubernetes.Interface` for K8s Secret operations\n  - `namespace string` for Secret namespace\n  - `logger Logger` for structured logging\n\n#### Scenario: RSA key generation\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n- **WHEN** generating RSA key\n- **THEN** `rsa.GenerateKey(rand.Reader, 2048)` SHALL be called\n- AND key size SHALL be `2048` bits (constant `rsaKeySize`)\n- AND private key SHALL be PKCS1 encoded\n- AND public key SHALL be PKIX encoded\n\n#### Scenario: GenerateToken\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n- **WHEN** calling `GenerateToken(ctx, kind, name, namespace)`\n- **THEN** JWT SHALL be created with claims:\n  - `exp` = `now + 5m` (constant `jwtExpiration`)\n  - `iat` = `now`\n  - `iss` = `\"agentcube-router\"`\n  - `kind` = kind parameter\n  - `name` = name parameter\n  - `namespace` = namespace parameter\n- AND JWT SHALL be signed with RS256 algorithm\n\n#### Scenario: TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret create\n- **GIVEN** no existing Secret `picod-router-identity`\n- **WHEN** calling `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx)`\n- **THEN** K8s Secret SHALL be created with:\n  - `name` = `IdentitySecretName` (`\"picod-router-identity\"`)\n  - `data[\"private-key\"]` = PKCS1 encoded private key\n  - `data[\"public-key\"]` = PKIX encoded public key\n\n#### Scenario: TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret load\n- **GIVEN** existing Secret `picod-router-identity`\n- **WHEN** calling `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx)`\n- **THEN** Secret SHALL be loaded via `kubeClient.CoreV1().Secrets(namespace).Get`\n- AND keys SHALL be decoded from Secret data\n- AND `privateKey` and `publicKey` SHALL be set from loaded data\n\n#### Scenario: TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret AlreadyExists\n- **GIVEN** multiple router replicas starting simultaneously\n- **WHEN** Secret creation returns `AlreadyExists` error\n- **THEN** existing Secret SHALL be loaded instead\n- AND no error SHALL be returned\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Middleware concurrency limit\n\nThe system SHALL limit concurrent requests using semaphore middleware.\n\n#### Scenario: concurrencyLimitMiddleware\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n- **WHEN** reading middleware implementation\n- **THEN** buffered channel SHALL be used as semaphore\n- AND channel capacity SHALL be `MaxConcurrentRequests`\n- AND default capacity SHALL be `1000` when `MaxConcurrentRequests <= 0`\n\n#### Scenario: Request acquires semaphore\n- **GIVEN** middleware with capacity 1000\n- **WHEN** request enters middleware\n- **THEN** `semaphore <- struct{}{}` SHALL acquire slot\n- AND request SHALL proceed if slot available\n\n#### Scenario: Semaphore full returns 429\n- **GIVEN** middleware with all slots occupied\n- **WHEN** new request enters middleware\n- **THEN** `select` with `default` case SHALL trigger\n- AND HTTP `429` SHALL be returned\n- AND response body SHALL have `SERVER_OVERLOADED` code\n\n#### Scenario: Request releases semaphore\n- **GIVEN** request completing processing\n- **WHEN** middleware exits\n- **THEN** `<-semaphore` SHALL release slot\n- AND deferred release SHALL guarantee cleanup\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Health handlers\n\nThe system SHALL implement health endpoints for Kubernetes probes.\n\n#### Scenario: handleHealthLive\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/handlers.go`\n- **WHEN** calling `/health/live`\n- **THEN** HTTP `200` SHALL be returned\n- AND body SHALL be `{\"status\":\"alive\"}`\n\n#### Scenario: handleHealthReady sessionManager nil\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/handlers.go`\n- **WHEN** calling `/health/ready` with `sessionManager == nil`\n- **THEN** HTTP `503` SHALL be returned\n- AND body SHALL indicate service unavailable\n\n#### Scenario: handleHealthReady sessionManager set\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/handlers.go`\n- **WHEN** calling `/health/ready` with valid `sessionManager`\n- **THEN** HTTP `200` SHALL be returned\n- AND body SHALL be `{\"status\":\"ready\"}`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Invocation handler\n\nThe system SHALL implement invocation handler for proxying requests to sandboxes.\n\n#### Scenario: handleInvoke extracts session ID\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/handlers.go`\n- **WHEN** processing invocation request\n- **THEN** `x-agentcube-session-id` header SHALL be read\n- AND session ID SHALL be extracted for session resolution\n\n#### Scenario: handleInvoke resolves session\n- **GIVEN** request with session ID header\n- **WHEN** processing invocation\n- **THEN** `sessionManager.GetSandboxBySession(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind)` SHALL be called\n- AND `namespace`, `name`, `kind` SHALL be extracted from URL path\n\n#### Scenario: handleInvoke creates new session\n- **GIVEN** request without session ID header\n- **WHEN** processing invocation\n- **THEN** new session ID SHALL be generated\n- AND new sandbox SHALL be created via session manager\n\n#### Scenario: handleInvoke proxies request\n- **GIVEN** resolved `SandboxInfo`\n- **WHEN** processing invocation\n- **THEN** reverse proxy SHALL forward request to `SandboxInfo.EntryPoints[0].Endpoint`\n- AND request body SHALL be forwarded unchanged\n\n#### Scenario: handleInvoke updates activity\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/handlers.go`\n- **WHEN** invocation completes\n- **THEN** `store.UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID)` SHALL be called\n- AND `LastActivity` timestamp SHALL be updated twice:\n  - After sandbox resolution\n  - After proxy completion\n\n#### Scenario: handleInvoke error mapping\n- **GIVEN** an error from session resolution or proxy\n- **WHEN** returning response\n- **THEN** error type SHALL map to HTTP code:\n  - `SessionNotFoundError` → `404`\n  - `SandboxUnreachableError` → `502`\n  - `TimeoutError` → `504`\n  - `JWTSigningFailedError` → `500`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Error types\n\nThe system SHALL define custom error types for categorizing failures.\n\n#### Scenario: SessionNotFoundError\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/errors.go`\n- **WHEN** reading error types\n- **THEN** `SessionNotFoundError` SHALL be defined\n- AND error code SHALL be `SESSION_NOT_FOUND`\n\n#### Scenario: SandboxUnreachableError\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/errors.go`\n- **WHEN** reading error types\n- **THEN** `SandboxUnreachableError` SHALL be defined\n- AND error code SHALL be `SANDBOX_UNREACHABLE`\n\n#### Scenario: TimeoutError\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/errors.go`\n- **WHEN** reading error types\n- **THEN** `TimeoutError` SHALL be defined\n- AND error code SHALL be `SANDBOX_TIMEOUT`\n\n#### Scenario: JWTSigningFailedError\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/errors.go`\n- **WHEN** reading error types\n- **THEN** `JWTSigningFailedError` SHALL be defined\n- AND error code SHALL be `JWT_SIGNING_FAILED`\n\n#### Scenario: ServerOverloadedError\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/errors.go`\n- **WHEN** reading error types\n- **THEN** `ServerOverloadedError` SHALL be defined\n- AND error code SHALL be `SERVER_OVERLOADED`\n\n#### Scenario: APIStatus interface\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/errors.go`\n- **WHEN** reading error types\n- **THEN** `APIStatus` interface SHALL be defined with:\n  - `Status() int` for HTTP status code\n  - `Code() string` for error code\n  - `Message() string` for error message\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Store interface usage\n\nThe system SHALL use Store interface for session state operations.\n\n#### Scenario: Store interface methods\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n- **WHEN** using Store interface\n- **THEN** methods SHALL be used:\n  - `GetSession(ctx, sessionID) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n  - `CreateSession(ctx, sandboxInfo) error`\n  - `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID) error`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Environment variables\n\nThe system SHALL read configuration from environment variables.\n\n#### Scenario: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n- **WHEN** initializing SessionManager\n- **THEN** `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable SHALL be required\n- AND startup SHALL fail if not set\n\n#### Scenario: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager.go`\n- **WHEN** determining namespace for sandbox creation\n- **THEN** `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` environment variable SHALL be read\n- AND default SHALL be `\"default\"` if not set\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Constants\n\nThe system SHALL define constants for configuration values.\n\n#### Scenario: rsaKeySize constant\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n- **WHEN** reading constants\n- **THEN** `rsaKeySize` SHALL be `2048`\n\n#### Scenario: jwtExpiration constant\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n- **WHEN** reading constants\n- **THEN** `jwtExpiration` SHALL be `5 * time.Minute`\n\n#### Scenario: IdentitySecretName constant\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n- **WHEN** reading constants\n- **THEN** `IdentitySecretName` SHALL be `\"picod-router-identity\"`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Unit tests for Server\n\nThe system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for Server behavior.\n\n#### Scenario: TestNewServer\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Constructor returns valid instance\n  - Gin mode is set correctly based on Debug config\n  - All fields are properly initialized\n\n#### Scenario: TestServer_StartTLS\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - TLS server starts with valid cert/key\n  - Error returned for missing cert/key files\n\n#### Scenario: TestServer_GracefulShutdown\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Server stops on context cancellation\n  - Shutdown deadline is 10s\n  - Existing requests complete before shutdown\n\n#### Scenario: TestServer_Routes\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/server_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Health routes are registered\n  - Invocation routes are registered\n  - Middleware chain is applied\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Unit tests for SessionManager\n\nThe system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for SessionManager.\n\n#### Scenario: TestNewSessionManager\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Constructor returns valid instance\n  - Fails when WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL not set\n  - HTTP client configured correctly\n\n#### Scenario: TestSessionManager_GetSandboxBySession_Existing\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests with existing session\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Store lookup is called\n  - SandboxInfo returned correctly\n\n#### Scenario: TestSessionManager_GetSandboxBySession_Create\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests with missing session\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - POST request sent to Workload Manager\n  - Correct endpoint based on kind\n  - Sandbox created and stored\n\n#### Scenario: TestSessionManager_createSandbox\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/session_manager_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Request body is CreateSandboxRequest\n  - K8s SA token added when available\n  - Error handling for failed requests\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Unit tests for ReverseProxy\n\nThe system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for reverse proxy.\n\n#### Scenario: TestReverseProxy_Director\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/reverse_proxy_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Path normalization adds leading slash\n  - Forwarding headers are set\n  - JWT is injected\n\n#### Scenario: TestReverseProxy_ModifyResponse\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/reverse_proxy_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Session ID header added to response\n\n#### Scenario: TestReverseProxy_ErrorHandler\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/reverse_proxy_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Connection refused → 502\n  - Timeout → 504\n  - Other errors → 500\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Unit tests for JWTManager\n\nThe system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for JWT operations.\n\n#### Scenario: TestJWTManager_GenerateToken\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Token contains correct claims\n  - Token is signed with RS256\n  - Token expires in 5 minutes\n\n#### Scenario: TestJWTManager_RSAKeyGeneration\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Key size is 2048 bits\n  - Keys are valid RSA keys\n\n#### Scenario: TestJWTManager_TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/jwt_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Secret created when not exists\n  - Secret loaded when exists\n  - AlreadyExists handled gracefully\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Unit tests for Middleware\n\nThe system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for concurrency middleware.\n\n#### Scenario: TestConcurrencyLimitMiddleware\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/middleware_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Requests proceed when slots available\n  - 429 returned when full\n  - Slots released after request completes\n\n#### Scenario: TestConcurrencyLimitMiddleware_DefaultCapacity\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/middleware_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests with MaxConcurrentRequests <= 0\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Capacity defaults to 1000\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Unit tests for Handlers\n\nThe system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for handlers.\n\n#### Scenario: TestHandleHealthLive\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/handlers_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Returns 200 with {\"status\":\"alive\"}\n\n#### Scenario: TestHandleHealthReady\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/handlers_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Returns 200 when sessionManager valid\n  - Returns 503 when sessionManager nil\n\n#### Scenario: TestHandleInvoke\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/handlers_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Session ID extracted from header\n  - New session created when missing\n  - Request proxied to sandbox endpoint\n  - Activity timestamp updated\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Unit tests for Errors\n\nThe system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for error types.\n\n#### Scenario: TestErrorTypes\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/errors_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - All error types implement APIStatus\n  - Status codes are correct\n  - Error codes are correct\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: File structure\n\nThe system SHALL organize router files correctly.\n\n#### Scenario: server.go location\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/`\n- **WHEN** listing files\n- **THEN** `server.go` SHALL exist with Server implementation\n\n#### Scenario: config.go location\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/`\n- **WHEN** listing files\n- **THEN** `config.go` SHALL exist with Config struct\n\n#### Scenario: session_manager.go location\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/`\n- **WHEN** listing files\n- **THEN** `session_manager.go` SHALL exist with SessionManager\n\n#### Scenario: reverse_proxy.go location\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/`\n- **WHEN** listing files\n- **THEN** `reverse_proxy.go` SHALL exist with proxy implementation\n\n#### Scenario: jwt.go location\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/`\n- **WHEN** listing files\n- **THEN** `jwt.go` SHALL exist with JWTManager\n\n#### Scenario: middleware.go location\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/`\n- **WHEN** listing files\n- **THEN** `middleware.go` SHALL exist with concurrency middleware\n\n#### Scenario: handlers.go location\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/`\n- **WHEN** listing files\n- **THEN** `handlers.go` SHALL exist with health and invocation handlers\n\n#### Scenario: errors.go location\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/`\n- **WHEN** listing files\n- **THEN** `errors.go` SHALL exist with error types\n\n#### Scenario: Test files location\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/router/`\n- **WHEN** listing files\n- **THEN** `*_test.go` SHALL exist for each implementation file\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `pkg/router/server.go` | HTTP Server with Gin engine, route registration, lifecycle |\n| `pkg/router/server_test.go` | Server unit tests |\n| `pkg/router/config.go` | Config struct with Port, TLS, MaxConcurrentRequests |\n| `pkg/router/config_test.go` | Config unit tests |\n| `pkg/router/session_manager.go` | SessionManager interface and implementation |\n| `pkg/router/session_manager_test.go` | SessionManager unit tests |\n| `pkg/router/reverse_proxy.go` | Reverse proxy with Director, ModifyResponse, ErrorHandler |\n| `pkg/router/reverse_proxy_test.go` | Reverse proxy unit tests |\n| `pkg/router/jwt.go` | JWTManager with RSA key generation, token signing |\n| `pkg/router/jwt_test.go` | JWT unit tests |\n| `pkg/router/middleware.go` | Concurrency limit middleware |\n| `pkg/router/middleware_test.go` | Middleware unit tests |\n| `pkg/router/handlers.go` | Health and invocation handlers |\n| `pkg/router/handlers_test.go` | Handlers unit tests |\n| `pkg/router/errors.go` | Error types with APIStatus interface |\n| `pkg/router/errors_test.go` | Error types unit tests |\n| `pkg/router/doc.go` | Package documentation |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | HTTP framework for routing and middleware |\n| `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | RS256 JWT signing |\n| `golang.org/x/net/http2` | h2c server configuration |\n| `net/http/httputil` | ReverseProxy for request forwarding |\n| `crypto/rsa` | RSA key generation and signing |\n| `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes` | Core Kubernetes API for Secret management |\n| `pkg/common/types` | SandboxInfo, CreateSandboxRequest/Response, kind constants |\n| `pkg/store` | Store interface for session lookup and activity updates |\n\n---\n\n## Request Flow\n\n```\nClient Request\n│\n├── Middleware Chain\n│   ├── concurrencyLimitMiddleware (semaphore acquire)\n│   ├── loggingMiddleware\n│   └── recoveryMiddleware\n│\n├── Handler: handleInvoke\n│   ├── Extract session ID from x-agentcube-session-id header\n│   ├── If missing: Generate new session ID\n│   │\n│   ├── SessionManager.GetSandboxBySession\n│   │   ├── Check store for existing session\n│   │   ├── If not found: createSandbox\n│   │   │   ├── POST to Workload Manager\n│   │   │   │   ├── /v1/agent-runtime (AgentRuntime)\n│   │   │   │   └── /v1/code-interpreter (CodeInterpreter)\n│   │   │   ├── With K8s SA token if available\n│   │   │   └── Store sandbox info\n│   │   └── Update activity timestamp (1st)\n│   │\n│   ├── ReverseProxy.ServeHTTP\n│   │   ├── Director\n│   │   │   ├── Path normalization (add leading slash)\n│   │   │   ├── Set Host, X-Forwarded-For, X-Real-IP\n│   │   │   ├── JWTManager.GenerateToken → Authorization header\n│   │   │   └── Target: SandboxInfo.EntryPoints[0].Endpoint\n│   │   ├── Forward to sandbox pod\n│   │   ├── ModifyResponse\n│   │   │   └── Add x-agentcube-session-id header\n│   │   └── ErrorHandler\n│   │       ├── Connection refused → 502\n│   │       └── Timeout → 504\n│   │\n│   └── Update activity timestamp (2nd)\n│\n└── Middleware Chain (exit)\n    └── concurrencyLimitMiddleware (semaphore release)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Error Mapping\n\n| Error Type | HTTP Status | Error Code | Condition |\n|------------|-------------|------------|-----------|\n| `SessionNotFoundError` | 404 | `SESSION_NOT_FOUND` | Session not in store |\n| `SandboxUnreachableError` | 502 | `SANDBOX_UNREACHABLE` | Connection refused to pod |\n| `TimeoutError` | 504 | `SANDBOX_TIMEOUT` | Proxy timeout |\n| `JWTSigningFailedError` | 500 | `JWT_SIGNING_FAILED` | JWT generation failure |\n| `ServerOverloadedError` | 429 | `SERVER_OVERLOADED` | Semaphore full |\n| `NoEntryPointError` | 404 | `NO_ENTRY_POINT` | Empty EntryPoints array |\n\n---\n\n## Configuration Values\n\n| Parameter | Default | Source | Description |\n|-----------|---------|--------|-------------|\n| `Port` | 8080 | Config | Listening port |\n| `EnableTLS` | false | Config | TLS enablement |\n| `TLSCert` | \"\" | Config | Certificate file path |\n| `TLSKey` | \"\" | Config | Private key file path |\n| `MaxConcurrentRequests` | 1000 | Config | Semaphore capacity |\n| `ReadTimeout` | 30s | Server | HTTP read timeout |\n| `IdleTimeout` | 90s | Server | HTTP idle timeout |\n| `ShutdownTimeout` | 10s | Server | Graceful shutdown deadline |\n| `rsaKeySize` | 2048 | Const | RSA key bits |\n| `jwtExpiration` | 5m | Const | JWT validity duration |\n| `IdentitySecretName` | picod-router-identity | Const | JWT Secret name |\n| `HttpClientTimeout` | 2m | SessionManager | HTTP client timeout |\n| `MaxIdleConnsPerHost` | 100 | SessionManager | Connection pool size |\n| `HTTP2ReadIdleTimeout` | 30s | SessionManager | HTTP2 read idle |\n| `HTTP2PingTimeout` | 15s | SessionManager | HTTP2 ping timeout |\n\n---\n\n## Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Usage |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------|\n| `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Yes | - | Workload Manager service URL |\n| `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | No | default | Namespace for sandbox creation |\n\n---\n\n## Validation Checklist\n\n- [ ] Server struct defined with all required fields\n- [ ] Config struct with Port, TLS, MaxConcurrentRequests\n- [ ] NewServer constructor initializes Gin engine\n- [ ] Gin mode set based on Debug config\n- [ ] Server.Start supports TLS and non-TLS\n- [ ] Graceful shutdown with 10s deadline\n- [ ] Health routes registered (/health/live, /health/ready)\n- [ ] Invocation routes registered with GET and POST\n- [ ] Middleware chain applied (concurrency, logging, recovery)\n- [ ] SessionManager interface defined\n- [ ] GetSandboxBySession resolves or creates sessions\n- [ ] createSandbox POST to Workload Manager\n- [ ] K8s SA token added for in-cluster auth\n- [ ] ReverseProxy with custom Director\n- [ ] Director normalizes path and injects JWT\n- [ ] ModifyResponse adds session header\n- [ ] ErrorHandler maps errors to HTTP codes\n- [ ] JWTManager with RSA key generation\n- [ ] GenerateToken with RS256, 5m expiration\n- [ ] TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret handles creation/loading\n- [ ] AlreadyExists handled for concurrent routers\n- [ ] concurrencyLimitMiddleware with semaphore\n- [ ] 429 returned when overloaded\n- [ ] handleHealthLive returns 200\n- [ ] handleHealthReady checks sessionManager\n- [ ] handleInvoke proxies to sandbox\n- [ ] Activity timestamp updated twice\n- [ ] Error types implement APIStatus\n- [ ] WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL required\n- [ ] AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE with default\n- [ ] Constants defined (rsaKeySize, jwtExpiration, IdentitySecretName)\n- [ ] Unit tests for all components\n- [ ] Pass `go vet` with zero issues\n- [ ] Pass `golangci-lint` with zero issues\n- [ ] Unit tests pass with >80% coverage"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/common/types/sandbox.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":60,"character":40},"end":{"line":60,"character":71}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#omitzero"},"source":"omitzero","message":"Omitempty has no effect on nested struct fields"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/go.mod":[{"range":{"start":{"line":49,"character":49},"end":{"line":49,"character":60}},"severity":2,"source":"go mod tidy","message":"k8s.io/utils should be direct"}]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-009/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-009/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775849324116,"end":1775849324146}}}}
